    <note>Cai(1) Qi [1646] Jinshi # 1. Fan(2) Zhongyan traces ancestry to the descendants of the Zhou founders who were enfeoffed in the state of Cai. No names after this early period (a number referenced in the Renming Da cidian for pre-Qin.) His great grandfather, Wan [3867], moved from Henan, Luoyang xian to Laizhou, Jiaoshui xian where he served as county magistrate, for nine consecutive years, and he ended his official career there. Yanqing's [1662] father, Jiao's [7068] elder brother, Juhou's [1650] granduncle. Jiao's father-in-law was Fan(2) Zhongyan [8043]. Qi was Liu(2) Xiang's [1200] father-in-law, and Kou(1) Ping's [899] maternal grandfather. See Zhang Fangping, 37.23b for patron-client relationsips. A nephew, Jian(2) [3854], used Qi's yin to enter the civil service. Jian(b) was Pei(1) Lun's [1395] father-in-law. Zhang Fangping, WJ, 37.1a-24b; Fan Chunren, WJ, 13.2b; Fan Zhongyan, WJ, 12.13a-15b, 14.5a; XCB, 102.17a, 103.5a, 104.5a, 112.10b, 113.9a, 123.10b; HSSCGY, 3.5b; Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 38.1a-3b; SS, 286.10a. CBD, 5, 3797-8.</note>
